India Bonds Drop, Rupee Pares Gains After RBI Rate Increase

-- B y   V   R a m a k r i s h n a n
-- 
2011-09-16T06:37:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/india-bonds-drop-rupee-pares-gains-after-rbi-rate-increase.html
India ’s bonds declined and the
rupee pared gains after the central bank increased borrowing
costs today.  The yield on the 7.80 percent note due April 2021 was at
8.36 percent as of 12:04 p.m. in Mumbai, compared with 8.32
percent before the policy announcement, according to the central
bank’s trading system. It closed at 8.33 percent yesterday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
V Ramakrishnan at 
 rvenkatarama@bloomberg.net  